comments.message:
Authcache's registrar config has the "ttl" up one level:

```
  "registration": {
    "domain": "authcache.staging.joyent.us",
    "type": "redis_host",
    "service": {
      "type": "service",
      "service": {
        "srvce": "_redis",
        "proto": "_tcp",
        "port": 6379
      },
      "ttl": 60
    },
    "ttl": 30
  },
```

Portolan and IMGAPI seem to have it at the level you describe here:

```
  "registration": {
    "domain": "portolan.staging-1.joyent.us",
    "type": "rr_host",
    "service": {
      "type": "service",
      "service": {
        "srvce": "_portolan",
        "proto": "_tcp",
        "ttl": 60,
        "port": 80
      }
    },
    "ttl": 60
  },
```

Is authcache's registrar config wrong here?
